731255f-c.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - Murphy Funeral.
731255f-c.text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events: A set of three views of
the funeral procession of Chas. Francis Murphy, former leader of Tammany
Hall, approaching St. Patrick's Cathedral. This individual died at his
home at 305 East 17th Street, on April 26, 1924 and this last mass was
held April 29, prior to interment in old Calvary Cemetery. In No's 1 and
2 the view is southward on Fifth Ave., across 49th Street and northward
in No. 3. For an account of this occurence and the life of the individual,
see,the New York Times of April 26 to 29, 1924.
April 29, 1924.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

713386f-a.title: Manhattan: 49th Street - 5th Avenue
713386f-a.text:
(1)
49th Street, west from Fifth Avenue, showing the houses along
''Speakeasy Row.'' During prohibition, most of these houses were
illegal saloons. One resident in this neighborhood was compelled
to place over his doorbell a card reading ''Private House,'' to avoid
being awakened at any hour by thirsty revellers. All of these
houses are now gone, and the site occupied by Rockefeller Centre.
August 18, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
